  "texts": [
    "However, it is important to acknowledge that this passive memristor crossbar array is susceptible to challenges related to sneak path current and cross-talk.",
    "The sneak path current denotes the unintended flow of current through other memristors when attempting to read a specific memristor, resulting in inaccurate readings and wastage of energy.",
    "The cross-talk issue emerges when a selected memristor receives a voltage pulse for weight updates, inadvertently causing 1 3 adjacent memristors to experience a half-voltage pulse, leading to current leakage and unintended alterations in their respective weights.",
    "These issues arise due to the inherent lack of precise control over current flow in this architecture.",
    "As a result, this passive crossbar array is most suitable for devices exhibiting high nonlinearities in their Fig. 4 Memristive array configurations and integrated in-memory circuits."
  ],
